Reasoning: The paper deals with achieving the optimal DMT (diversity-multiplexing tradeoff) of selective fading MIMO (multiple-input multiple-output) channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The paper also proposes a new code construction, which involves parallel coding and splitting, making it relevant to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper's focus on achieving optimal performance in a specific type of channel could also make it relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
